{"questionId":"9077051","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In an investigation to measure the acceleration of free fall a rod is suspended horizontally by&nbsp;two vertical strings of equal length. The strings are a distance<em> d</em> apart.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/eaa214425e2416bb97246b2c9ebcd06171668baf.png\"></p>\n<p>When the rod is displaced by a small angle and then released, simple harmonic oscillations&nbsp;take place in a horizontal plane.</p>\n<p>The theoretical prediction for the period of oscillation<em> T</em> is given by the following equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T = \\frac{c}{{d\\sqrt g }}\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mi>g</mi>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <em>c</em> is a known numerical constant.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the unit of <em>c</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{m^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept other power of tens multiples of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{m^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, eg:&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{cm^{\\frac{3}{2}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077051","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the unit of c.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}